parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates on the dashboard
total brake failure
hydroplaning
sliding or loss of control while braking
hard brake pedal
low brake fluid warning
and erratic operation of the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the odometer can cause the vehicle's mileage to be unknown, making it difficult to determine when maintenance is required, and potentially leading to safety issues.
symptoms: The odometer does not display the correct mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the serpentine belt or tensioner can cause the belt to slip or fall off, leading to loss of power steering, engine noise, stalling, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The serpentine belt pops off
the belt slips
the power steering fails
the engine makes noise
the engine stalls
the belt falls off without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cylinder Head Failure (Rocker Arm Support Tower)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cylinder head's rocker arm support tower can cause severe valve lash, requiring the complete replacement of both cylinder heads, which can lead to engine damage and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The rocker arm support tower detaches from the cylinder head
severe valve lash occurs
the engine makes noise
the engine stalls.
